Reasoning: The paper discusses the limitations of worst-case analysis in certain computational problems and proposes modeling methods to go beyond it. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to sub-categories related to algorithms, machine learning, and optimization. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as it directly deals with algorithmic analysis. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as they deal with modeling and optimization techniques. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as it is mentioned in the abstract as one of the computational problems where worst-case analysis is not helpful. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but it is still possible as the paper may discuss modeling methods for analyzing network data.
